MySQL Basic Concepts
Database â†’ Folder
Table â†’ File
Schema â†’ Database structure
Database name â†’ Acts like a filename


ğŸ”´ğŸŸ¡ğŸŸ¢Database Commands
ğŸŸ Create Database
CREATE DATABASE database_name;

ğŸŸ£Use Database
USE database_name;                                       OR         Set it as Default Schema in MySQL Workbench.

ğŸŸ£Drop (Delete) Database
DROP DATABASE database_name;

ğŸŸ£Read-Only Mode :: Enable Read-Only Mode
ALTER DATABASE database_name READ ONLY = 1;
Database cannot be dropped while in read-only mode.

ğŸŸ£Disable Read-Only Mode
ALTER DATABASE database_name READ ONLY = 0;

ğŸŸ£Creating a Table
CREATE TABLE EMPLOYEE (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    id INT,
    salary DECIMAL(5,3),
    hire_date DATE
);

ğŸŸ£Data Types Explained
VARCHAR(50) â†’ String (max 50 characters)
INT â†’ Integer
DECIMAL(5,3) â†’  5 digits total   3 digits after decimal point
DATE â†’ Stores date (YYYY-MM-DD)

âš ï¸ Note:
No comma after the last column
End statement with ;

ğŸŸ£Select Data
Select All Records from a Table
SELECT * FROM table_name;

ğŸŸ£Drop Table
DROP TABLE table_name;

ğŸŸ£Alter Table
Add a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name
ADD phone_number INT;

ğŸŸ£Modify a Column            
ALTER TABLE table_name                        OR                        ALTER TABLE table_name
MODIFY num INT                                                           MODIFY num INT FIRST;
AFTER name;                             

ğŸŸ£Drop a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name
DROP COLUMN hire_date;

ğŸŸ£Rename a Column
ALTER TABLE table_name                 
RENAME COLUMN old_name TO new_name;                                      

Example
ALTER TABLE work
RENAME COLUMN day TO date;
